title: Bean and Brew
text:
Impact & Results
Our team was awarded Second Place for our ability to translate these statistical findings into actionable business recommendations.


The Challenge

Analyze whether the current promotions work, and what other business strategies can we recommend to promote reusable cup usage.
Trying to strike the balance between environmental protection and profit generation.



What we did

Data set cleaning & joining: calculated product profit from items, merged it to the sales dataset, added cup profit to finally get total profit per transaction
EDA: visualize financial and environmental performance before/after Nov 2023
Statistical analysis: z-test
Simple modeling: Logistic Regression

title: Hotdog Predictor
text:
Can a business name reveal whatâ€™s on the menu? This project explores text-based classification using the City of Vancouverâ€™s Street Food Vending dataset.
I engineered a binary target from vendor descriptions and trained multiple models, including Decision Trees and Logistic Regression, to identify hot dog vendors based solely on their business names. After rigorous cross-validation, a tuned NaÃ¯ve Bayes classifier emerged as the top performer with 79% accuracy. The project highlights the challenges of imbalanced datasets and the nuances of classifying minority target classes in urban data.
